The paper deals with target tracking in a camera network, which is a problem in computer vision and robotics. The use of reinforcement learning and Q-learning suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of spatial and temporal information also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
